cs.HC, cs.ED, cs.AI, cs.CYBER, cs.DL 

The paper discusses the use of science fiction in Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) education, which is a subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.HC is the most likely category. The paper also discusses education and learning, which suggests cs.ED as a likely category. The use of science fiction as a means to analyze yet-to-come HCI technologies suggests cs.AI and cs.CYBER as possible categories. Finally, the paper mentions the Framework for 21st Century Learning, which involves skills such as critical thinking and problem solving, suggesting cs.DL as a possible category.
